## Product Purpose

Google Vision may identify landmarks or recognizable places from image content.

Examples:

```
Saddleback CollegeDisneylandEmpire State BuildingGolden Gate BridgeMission San Juan Capistrano
```

These are useful only if the user can review and confirm them.

The system should treat Vision output as provider evidence:

```
Vision result = candidate observationUser decision = accepted/rejected/ignored/link/createCanonical Place truth = only after user action
```

---

## Core Principle

Do not treat Google Vision results as automatic truth.

For this milestone:

```
Accepting a landmark observation does not automatically assign every similar photo.Accepting a landmark observation does not automatically overwrite Place data.Creating a new Place requires explicit user confirmation.Linking to an existing Place requires explicit user confirmation.
```

