# Answers to Coder Questions — Milestone 12.60.1

## 1. Placement

Yes. Put the new landmark review area inside the existing **Places view** for 12.60.1.

Preferred UI location:

```text
Places view
  Existing Places list/detail
  New section/tab/panel:
    Google Vision Landmark Observations

Do not create a separate Admin screen yet.

Reason:

Landmark observations are part of the Place workflow.
Keeping review inside Places view reduces navigation complexity for v1.
2. No-coordinate Create Place behavior

Yes. If the current Place model requires non-null representative latitude/longitude, block Create Place when the Vision observation has no lat/lon.

Preferred message:

This landmark observation does not include coordinates, so a new Place cannot be created from it yet.
You can link it to an existing Place instead.

Do not invent coordinates.

Do not use asset GPS as a fallback in 12.60.1 unless explicitly reviewed in a later milestone.

Reason:

Create Place from Vision should be deterministic and evidence-based.
If Vision did not return coordinates, we should not guess.

Future option:

Allow create Place without coordinates if the Place model is relaxed later.

But not in 12.60.1.

3. Link/Create side effects

Confirmed.

Both actions should automatically set the observation status to accepted:

Link to Existing Place:
  observation.place_id = selected Place
  observation.status = accepted
  asset.place_id unchanged

Create New Place:
  create Place
  observation.place_id = new Place
  observation.status = accepted
  asset.place_id unchanged

Important:

Do not change asset.place_id in 12.60.1.

That will be a separate review/assignment milestone if needed.

4. Accept-only semantics

Confirmed.

Accept-only behavior:

If observation is unlinked:
  status = accepted
  place_id remains null

If observation is already linked:
  status = accepted
  existing place_id remains unchanged

Accept-only means:

User accepts the Vision result as valid evidence,
but does not necessarily link/create a Place yet.
5. Place picker source

Yes. Use the existing Places list/search from places.py for the picker in 12.60.1.

Do not add a separate dedicated picker endpoint unless current API shape is insufficient.

Minimum picker behavior:

search/list existing Places
select one
confirm link

The picker should benefit from existing place search behavior, including aliases if already wired.

6. Review list default filter

Default to pending only.

Preferred:

default filter:
  pending

optional if quick:
  pending / accepted / rejected / ignored

Minimum acceptable for 12.60.1:

show pending Google Vision landmark observations only

But adding a simple status filter is useful if low-risk.

